data.NARR: When working in the field, there are cases in which the strut assembly cannot be easily removed depending on the vehicle model. If there is not enough work space, first remove the surrounding parts as much as possible to secure space, and then remove it carefully so as not to damage the internal sound absorbing material or anti-rust coating. When disassembling, remembering the path where the parts come out makes assembly easier even when assembling.
data.TITLE: Remove the strut assembly

data.TITLE: Remove the strut assembly

data.NARR: Attach the strut assembly to the spring compressor.
data.TITLE: Disassemble the strut assembly
data.PRCTN: When combining the strut assembly, level it with the compressor.

data.NARR: Join the bottom of the strut assembly.
Join the top of the strut assembly.

A spring compressor is a device that causes many human and material accidents in the field. If the spring is compressed with the spring fixing bracket incorrectly installed, the spring may bounce off and hit the operator's face in an accident.
data.TITLE: Remove the strut assembly

data.NARR: Therefore, in the field, by connecting the spring and the spring compressor with a chain, the chain connected to the spring compressor blocks the spring even if the spring bounces off, thereby promoting worker safety.
Compress the spring by turning the handle clockwise until the spring disengages.
data.TITLE: Disassemble the strut assembly
data.PRCTN: When working, secure the compressor using feet or a fixed object to prevent it from shaking. If the spring and compressor are out of horizontal when compressing, rotate the compression handle counterclockwise to slowly return, level it up, and then compress it again.
